📄 the problem statement 
in today’s digital world, people use passwords for almost everything like social media, banking, emails, and for various things. however, many users create 
passwords(weak) that are easy to guess putting their personal data at risk.the main objective of this project is to build a system that can 
evaluate the strength of a password based on things like the length, use of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters. 
this helps users understand how secure their password is and guides them in creating stronger ones. 

🔧 this resolves issues like:
users creating weak or predictable passwords 
lack of awareness about password security 
risk of unauthorized access to personal accounts

📌 scope of the project 
this project focuses on: 
rule-based password strength checking 
analyzing password composition (length, characters, etc.) 
classifying passwords as weak, medium, or strong 
providing feedback to improve password quality 

❌ the project does not include: 
advanced ai or machine learning models
real-time hacking simulations 
integration with live authentication systems 

🧑‍🤝‍🧑 target users 
students learning programming concepts 
general users who want to create secure passwords 
developers building basic security tools 
anyone interested in improving password safety 

🔍 high-level features 
password input and analysis 
strength classification (weak / medium / strong) 
simple and easy-to-use interface 
fast and efficient checking system 
basic suggestions for improvement
